## SD Card Configuration (from Phase 4)

The SD card was mounted in `main.c` using the **SDMMC 1‑bit mode** with the following verified pins for your CrowPanel v1.0 board:

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| **CLK** | GPIO 36 |
| **CMD** | GPIO 35 |
| **D0** | GPIO 37 |
| **Bus width** | 1‑bit |
| **Mount point** | `/sdcard` |
| **Filesystem** | FAT32 (no auto‑format) |

The exact code used:

```c
#define SDMMC_CLK_IO  36
#define SDMMC_CMD_IO  35
#define SDMMC_D0_IO   37

static bool mount_sdcard(void) {
    sdmmc_host_t host = SDMMC_HOST_DEFAULT();
    host.slot = SDMMC_HOST_SLOT_0;
    host.max_freq_khz = SDMMC_FREQ_DEFAULT;

    sdmmc_slot_config_t slot_config = SDMMC_SLOT_CONFIG_DEFAULT();
    slot_config.clk = SDMMC_CLK_IO;
    slot_config.cmd = SDMMC_CMD_IO;
    slot_config.d0  = SDMMC_D0_IO;
    slot_config.width = 1;

    esp_vfs_fat_mount_config_t mount_config = {
        .format_if_mount_failed = false,
        .max_files = 5,
        .allocation_unit_size = 16 * 1024
    };

    sdmmc_card_t *card;
    esp_err_t ret = esp_vfs_fat_sdmmc_mount("/sdcard", &host, &slot_config,
                                             &mount_config, &card);
    // ...
}
```

The model files were placed in `/sdcard/models/p4/` and the database path was `/sdcard/faces.db`.

